util.searchable

Class ProductCategoryFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • util.searchable.ProductCategoryFilter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ISearchFilter

    public class ProductCategoryFilter
extends Object
implements ISearchFilter
    Implements the ISearchFilter interface and defines a filter strategy based on the ProductCategory of an IProduct. This means, that the ProductCategorys are compared. An example for this filter is to filter all IProducts from an ITree that match a ProductCategory.

    • Method Detail

      • searchFilterFunction

        public boolean searchFilterFunction(Object originalObject,
                                    Object compareObject)
        Returns true if the two arguments match and their ProductCategory are equal. The original object and the compare object may be an IProduct or a ProductCategory. In the first case the ProductCategory is extracted from the IProduct.

        If one of the passed objects is NULL the filter function will return FALSE.

        Specified by:
        searchFilterFunction in interface ISearchFilter
        Parameters:
        originalObject - the object that is to be checked
        compareObject - the object we compare against
        Returns:
        TRUE if the filter matches, FALSE otherwise
